description: Adjust the sensitivity potentiometer to test if the threshold for the relay switching can be stabilized, or if the circuit continues to oscillate. Observe the effect on oscillation and lamp behavior., outcome='The sensitivity potentiometer adjustment did not stabilize the circuit; the system remains in an unstable or oscillating state according to the simulation. The control relay is observed to be closed, and the main load (lamp) is lit with no observable internal faults in either component.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('adjust_potentiometer', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> light sensor in the ambient sensor module,
description: Measure the voltage output from the light sensor under current ambient conditions to check if it is generating a fluctuating or noisy signal that could be causing the relay oscillation., outcome='Voltage readings at the ambient light sensor are 5.9373 V (positive terminal) and 0.023 V (negative terminal) with respect to ground. The simulation indicates the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state; measurement completed successfully. No polarity inversion was observed in this step.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> relay control input in ambient sensor module,
description: Measure the voltage at the relay coil control input with respect to ground to verify if the relay is being driven by a clean DC level or if there is oscillation or noise at this node. This will help determine whether the issue stems from the light sensor circuit or the relay driver circuitry., outcome='Voltage measurement at the control relay shows nearly equal potentials at both probe points (11.8516 V and 11.8505 V w.r.t. ground), indicating no clear DC drive and suggesting oscillation or instability at this node. The simulation did not converge, confirming the unstable or oscillating circuit state.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> wiring between light sensor and relay control circuit in ambient sensor module,
description: Inspect and test the wiring and connections between the sensor output and the relay control circuit, looking for potential intermittent connections, poor solder joints, or short circuits that could introduce instability., outcome='All measured resistances are nominal, and physical connections have been inspected. No short circuits or poor solder joints were detected, but the simulation did not converge and indicated circuit instability. POLARITY INVERSION NOT DETECTED in the connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=95.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> sensor-operated relay in ambient sensor module,
description: Test the relay operation directly by observing its switching response in real time, checking for chatter or rapid switching. This will help determine if the relay itself is defective or if the instability is purely upstream., outcome='Inspection panel was successfully opened, allowing access to internal components. The Control Relay was visually inspected and observed to be closed. However, the simulation did not converge, indicating the circuit is in an unstable or oscillating state; no observable internal faults were detected in the relay.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=15.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module power supply terminals,
description: Measure the DC voltage across the power supply terminals inside the ambient sensor module to check for stable voltage. This will determine if the power supply to the control circuit is steady or contributing to oscillation., outcome='DC voltage measurements at the control input cable terminals show 11.86\u202fV at (+) and 0.012\u202fV at (−), indicating a nominal polarity across the control input. The circuit is currently unstable or oscillating, as noted by the simulation not converging.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> feedback path and ground connection in ambient sensor module,
description: Test for unexpected feedback paths or inappropriate grounding by measuring voltages and continuity around the comparator or controller circuit that interprets the light sensor output. Look for ground loops or possible feedback short-circuits that could explain the persistent oscillation., outcome='All measured cables, sensor, resistor, and relay show nominal continuity. Voltage measurements indicate expected positive and near-ground levels at the labeled (+) and (−) cables; no POLARITY INVERSION detected. The circuit is reported as unstable or oscillating, but no ground loops, feedback short-circuits, or polarity inversions are indicated by these results.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=405.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> ambient sensor module circuit board and components,
description: Carefully visually inspect the ambient sensor module circuit board, focusing on any added or stray passive components (capacitors, resistors) or wiring around the relay driver circuitry, looking for unexpected modifications, loose components, or evidence of an incorrectly connected or missing element that could cause oscillation., outcome='All inspected components—the Ambient Light Sensor, Control Relay, and Sensor Bias Resistor—show no observable internal faults, and the inspection panel is open for further measurements. The relay is closed, and no unexpected modifications or loose elements were detected during visual inspection. However, note that the simulation did not converge, indicating circuit instability or oscillation remains unresolved.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=35.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
